# Repository pattern

Maximum decomposition within each module. Data flows through layers; each layer has one responsibility.

## Layer flow

```
Controller / Livewire / Filament page
        ↓
    Service          ← business logic, orchestration
        ↓
   Repository        ← queries, persistence
        ↓
      Model           ← Eloquent entity only
```

## Rules

- ❌ Controllers must **not** call Eloquent models or `Model::query()` directly.
- ❌ Services must **not** embed raw query logic — delegate to repositories.
- ❌ Repositories must **not** contain business rules (validation, workflows, notifications).
- ✅ Controllers are thin: receive request → call service → return response/view.
- ✅ Services express use cases (`listProductsForStorefront`, `placeOrder`, etc.).
- ✅ Repositories encapsulate all DB access for one aggregate (e.g. `ProductRepository`).

## Shared infrastructure (`app/`)

```
app/Repositories/
├── Contracts/RepositoryInterface.php   ← thin common contract (find, findOrFail)
└── Eloquent/EloquentRepository.php     ← abstract base for all Eloquent repos
```

## Module layout

```
Modules/{Module}/app/
├── Http/
│   ├── Controllers/
│   └── Requests/         ← Form Request classes (see form-requests.mdc)
├── Services/
└── Repositories/
    ├── Contracts/        ← entity interfaces (extend RepositoryInterface)
    └── Eloquent/         ← concrete implementations (extend EloquentRepository)
```

Register entity repository bindings in the module `ServiceProvider`.

## Cross-module (unchanged)

- Order module still must **not** import Catalog models or repositories.
- Inter-module reads/writes go through `app/Contracts/` + DTOs; contract implementations may use repositories internally.

## Example (Catalog storefront)

```php
// Controller
public function index(ProductListingService $service): View
{
    return view('catalog::products.index', [
        'products' => $service->listForStorefront(),
    ]);
}

// Service → Repository → Model
```

## Filament

- Filament Resources/Pages follow the same rule: call a **service**, not a model directly.
- Table/form configuration may stay in the Resource; data loading and mutations go through services.
